e `!` and `?`).\n- **Toxicity Regex**: Searching for specific aggressive or insult keywords. Often class 2 represents toxicity.\n- Enhancing **Metadata**: Dealing with missing specific columns and log-scaling right-skewed numericals (upvotes/downvotes).\n","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"# A regex to capture hostility or strong emotion words. \n# This often helps separate negative/insulting comments (likely a specific label) without needing heavy NLP libraries.\nswear_pattern = re.compile(r'\\b(idiot|stupid|dumb|fake|liar|hate|hell|damn|shit|fuck|bitch|asshole|crap|bullshit|trash|garbage)\\b', re.IGNORECASE)\n\n# Helper function to engineer features\ndef engineer_features(df):\n    # 1. Handle Missing Data\n    df['comment']  = df['comment'].fillna('')\n    df['race']     = df['race'].fillna('missing').astype(str)\n    df['religion'] = df['religion'].fillna('missing').astype(str)\n    df['gender']   = df['gender'].fillna('missing').astype(str)\n    \n    # 2. Text Metadata\n    c = df['comment']\n    df['comment_length'] = c.apply(len)\n    df['word_count']     = c.str.split().str.len().fillna(0).astype(int)\n    df['avg_word_len']   = df['comment_length'] / (df['word_count'] + 1)\n    \n    # Diversity of text\n    df['unique_word_count'] = c.apply(lambda x: len(set(x.lower().split())))\n    df['unique_word_ratio'] = df['unique_word_count'] / (df['word_count'] + 1)\n    \n    # Punctuation & Emotion\n    df['excl_count']    = c.str.count('!')\n    df['ques_count']    = c.str.count(r'\\?')\n    df['capital_count'] = c.apply(lambda x: sum(1 for ch in x if ch.isupper()))\n    df['capital_ratio'] = df['capital_count'] / (df['comment_length'] + 1)\n    \n    # Keyword matches\n    df['toxic_count']   = c.apply(lambda x: len(swear_pattern.findall(x)))\n    \n    # Time Data\n    df['created_date'] = pd.to_datetime(df['created_date'], errors='coerce')\n    df['hour']         = df['created_date'].dt.hour.fillna(0).astype(int)\n    df['dayofweek']    = df['created_date'].dt.dayofweek.fillna(0).astype(int)\n    \n    # Numeric Transformations\n    df['log_upvote']   = np.log1p(df['upvote'])\n    df['log_downvote'] = np.log1p(df['downvote'])\n    \n    # Engagement ratio\n    df['upvotes_per_word'] = df['upvote'] / (df['word_count'] + 1)\n    \n    return df\n\nprint(\"Applying feature engineering to train...\")\ntrain = engineer_features(train)\nprint(\"Applying feature engineering to test...\")\ntest = engineer_features(test)\n\n# One-hot encode the categorical variables\ntrain = pd.get_dummies(train, columns=['race', 'religion', 'gender'])\ntest  = pd.get_dummies(test,  columns=['race', 'religion', 'gender'])\n\n# Align train and test explicitly keeping only columns present in both (ignoring label)\ntrain, test = train.align(test, join='left', axis=1, fill_value=0)\nprint(f\"Train engineered shapes: {train.shape}, Test engineered shapes: {test.shape}\")\n","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-03-29T17:22:55.444275Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-03-29T17:22:55.444547Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-03-29T17:23:08.701027Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-03-29T17:22:55.444527Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-03-29T17:23:08.700143Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","text":"Applying feature engineering to train...\nApplying feature engineering to test...\nTrain engineered shapes: (198000, 49), Test engineered shapes: (102000, 49)\n","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":6},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## 5. TF-IDF Text Vectorization\nWe use a dual approach:\n1. **Word TF-IDF**: Captures full meaningful words and bigrams.\n2. **Char-wb TF-IDF**: Captures subwords, morphology, and resists misspellings/slang!\n\n*Note: Dimensionality is kept slightly constrained (20k each) to handle memory nicely during hyperparameter tuning.*\n","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"print('Fitting Word-level TF-IDF...')\nword_tfidf = TfidfVectorizer(\n    max_features=25000,\n    ngram_range=(1, 2),\n    stop_words='english',\n    sublinear_tf=True,\n    min_df=2,\n    max_df=0.95\n)\nX_word      = word_tfidf.fit_transform(train['comment'])\nX_test_word = word_tfidf.transform(test['comment'])\n\nprint('Fitting Char-level TF-IDF...')\nchar_tfidf = TfidfVectorizer(\n    max_features=25000,\n    analyzer='char_wb',\n    ngram_range=(3, 5),\n    sublinear_tf=True,\n    min_df=2,\n    max_df=0.95\n)\nX_char      = char_tfidf.fit_transform(train['comment'])\nX_test_char = char_tfidf.transform(test['comment'])\n\n# Combine NLP with numeric features\nskip_cols = ['comment', 'label', 'created_date', 'upvote', 'downvote']\nnum_cols  = [c for c in train.columns if c not in skip_cols]\n\n# Cast numerics to float32 to save RAM\nX_num      = train[num_cols].apply(pd.to_numeric, errors='coerce').fillna(0).astype('float32')\nX_test_num = test[num_cols].apply(pd.to_numeric,  errors='coerce').fillna(0).astype('float32')\n\nprint(\"Stacking matrices into CSR sparse arrays...\")\nX      = hstack([X_word, X_char, csr_matrix(X_num.values)])\nX_test = hstack([X_test_word, X_test_char, csr_matrix(X_test_num.values)])\n\nprint(f'Train Features shape: {X.shape}')\nprint(f'Test Features shape:  {X_test.shape}')\n\n# Target labels\nle = LabelEncoder()\ny  = le.fit_transform(train['label'])\n","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-03-29T17:23:08.702315Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-03-29T17:23:08.702558Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-03-29T17:25:21.789050Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-03-29T17:23:08.702533Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-03-29T17:25:21.788500Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","text":"Fitting Word-level TF-IDF...\nFitting Char-level TF-IDF...\nStacking matrices into CSR sparse arrays...\nTrain Features shape: (198000, 50044)\nTest Features shape:  (102000, 50044)\n","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":7},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## 6. Training & Validation Setup\nWe'll split a validation set using `stratify=y` to maintain the highly imbalanced class proportions. We will test multiple models simultaneously.\n","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"X_train, X_val, y_train, y_val = train_test_split(\n    X, y, test_size=0.15, random_state=42, stratify=y\n)\nprint(f\"X_train size: {X_train.shape[0]} | X_val size: {X_val.shape[0]}\")\n","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-03-29T17:25:21.789752Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-03-29T17:25:21.789952Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-03-29T17:25:22.086643Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-03-29T17:25:21.789932Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-03-29T17:25:22.085832Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","text":"X_train size: 168300 | X_val size: 29700\n","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":8},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## 7. Model Building & Hyperparameter Tuning\n\nWe will add **SGDClassifier** (Linear SVM proxy), **RidgeClassifier**, **XGBoostClassifier** alongside the previous ones.\n*Note: Due to the 200k rows, we utilize fast parameters.*\n","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"# 7.1 Multinomial Naive Bayes (Fast baseline)\nprint(\"Training Naive Bayes...\")\nnb = MultinomialNB(alpha=0.08) # slightly strict smoothing\nnb.fit(X_train, y_train)\nnb_pred = nb.predict(X_val)\nprint(f\"NB Validation Accuracy: {accuracy_score(y_val, nb_pred):.4f}\")\n\n# 7.2 Logistic Regression (Randomized Search)\nprint(\"\\nTuning Logistic Regression...\")\nlr = LogisticRegression(max_iter=500, solver='lbfgs', random_state=42, class_weight='balanced')\nlr_params = {'C': stats.uniform(0.1, 8.0)}\nlr_rs = RandomizedSearchCV(lr, lr_params, n_iter=3, cv=2, scoring='accuracy', random_state=42, n_jobs=-1)\nlr_rs.fit(X_train, y_train)\nbest_lr = lr_rs.best_estimator_\nprint(f\"Best LR Params: {lr_rs.best_params_}\")\nprint(f\"LR Validation Accuracy: {accuracy_score(y_val, best_lr.predict(X_val)):.4f}\")\n\n# 7.3 SGD Classifier (Linear SVM - Super Fast for massive Sparse text data)\nprint(\"\\nTraining SGDClassifier...\")\n# modified_huber loss enables us to extract smooth probabilities later via predict_proba\nsgd = SGDClassifier(loss='modified_huber', penalty='l2', alpha=1e-4, max_iter=1000, \n                    random_state=42, class_weight='balanced')\nsgd.fit(X_train, y_train)\nprint(f\"SGD Validation Accuracy: {accuracy_score(y_val, sgd.predict(X_val)):.4f}\")\n\n# 7.4 LightGBM Classifier\nprint(\"\\nTraining LightGBM...\")\nlgb_model = lgb.LGBMClassifier(\n    n_estimators=300,\n    learning_rate=0.08,\n    num_leaves=64,\n    max_depth=8,\n    random_state=42,\n    n_jobs=-1,\n    verbose=-1,\n    is_unbalance=True  # extremely crucial to handle class 3\n)\nlgb_model.fit(X_train, y_train)\nprint(f\"LGB Validation Accuracy: {accuracy_score(y_val, lgb_model.predict(X_val)):.4f}\")\n\n# 7.5 XGBoost Classifier\nprint(\"\\nTraining XGBoost...\")\nxgb_model = xgb.XGBClassifier(\n    n_estimators=250,\n    learning_rate=0.1,\n    max_depth=7,\n    random_state=42,\n    n_jobs=-1,\n    objective='multi:softprob',\n    eval_metric='mlogloss',\n    tree_method='hist' # hist method works well with sparse text data\n)\nxgb_model.fit(X_train, y_train)\nprint(f\"XGB Validation Accuracy: {accuracy_score(y_val, xgb_model.predict(X_val)):.4f}\")\n","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-03-29T17:25:22.087579Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-03-29T17:25:22.087839Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","text":"Training Naive Bayes...\nNB Validation Accuracy: 0.4602\n\nTuning Logistic Regression...\n","output_type":"stream"},{"name":"stderr","text":"/usr/local/lib/python3.12/dist-packages/sklearn/linear_model/_logistic.py:465: ConvergenceWarning: lbfgs failed to converge (status=1):\nSTOP: TOTAL NO. OF ITERATIONS REACHED LIMIT.\n\nIncrease the number of iterations (max_iter) or scale the data as shown in:\n    https://scikit-learn.org/stable/modules/preprocessing.html\nPlease also refer to the documentation for alternative solver options:\n    https://scikit-learn.org/stable/modules/linear